# SpeakFit Shadcn/Tailwind UI Contract Rule

When creating or modifying SpeakFit frontend UI, do not depend on `cursor/canvas` internals. The Canvas source is only a visual and interaction reference. Preserve the UI direction, color mood, visual hierarchy, layout shape, and flow; do not treat Canvas preview pixel dimensions as binding production specs.

Before frontend UI work, read and follow:

1. `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md`
2. `DESIGN.md`
3. `docs/ui-ux/speakfit-quiet-studio-reference.md`
4. `docs/ui-ux/shadcn-tailwind-implementation-contract.md`
5. `.cursor/rules/speakfit-ui-ux-reference.mdc`

Production implementation must translate Canvas roles into project-owned `shadcn/ui` + Tailwind wrappers.

Required mapping discipline:

- `Button` -> project button wrapper built on `shadcn/ui` `Button` with SpeakFit variants.
- `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardBody` -> `SpeakFitCard` wrappers around shadcn card primitives.
- `Grid`, `Row`, `Stack` -> project layout wrappers or consistent Tailwind grid/flex utilities.
- `Pill` -> quiet badge/status wrapper.
- `Stat` -> lightweight metric wrapper.
- `H1`, `H2`, `H3`, `Text` -> project typography wrappers or consistent typography variants.
- `useCanvasState` -> normal production state: React state, URL state, persisted settings, or server state as appropriate.
- `useHostTheme` -> Tailwind/theme-provider tokens.

Preferred production UI kit location:

- `src/components/speakfit/ui/`

Do not:

- import `cursor/canvas` into app code,
- copy Canvas-only APIs as production dependencies,
- rebuild the UI with arbitrary raw Tailwind classes on every page,
- replace the Quiet Studio shell with a generic dashboard or chatbot-first UI,
- add heavy gamification, leaderboard, IELTS/report-card scoring, or course-marketplace expansion unless the PRD is updated.

Preserve:

- desktop-first app shell with sidebar and top navbar,
- `Today` three-area workspace: mission rail, rehearsal stage, coach panel,
- mission loop: `Warm-up -> Shadow -> Record -> Feedback -> Fallback -> Complete`,
- learner pages: `Onboarding`, `Today`, `Missions`, `Phrases`, `Progress`, `Settings`,
- internal gated `Operator` page,
- Quiet Studio color mood, visual hierarchy, and supportive coach tone,
- privacy trust layer and manual text fallback.

Production sizing is flexible. Exact Canvas widths, heights, and spacing are not binding; adapt them to the real web viewport while keeping the same perceived layout and UX hierarchy.

If implementation must deviate from the Canvas reference, document the reason in the relevant planning artifact or work order before coding.
